1
00:00:39,070 --> 00:00:40,540
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

2
00:00:40,540 --> 00:00:41,970
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

3
00:00:43,780 --> 00:00:45,450
I was just organizing some books.

4
00:00:45,850 --> 00:00:47,980
- Did you have lunch?
- A little while ago.

5
00:00:48,050 --> 00:00:50,050
- What about you?
- No.

6
00:00:50,380 --> 00:00:51,980
I should starve a little
to fit into my tuxedo.

7
00:00:53,050 --> 00:00:54,850
You're joking, right?

8
00:00:54,990 --> 00:00:56,220
A joke would be a waste of time.

9
00:00:56,490 --> 00:00:58,020
I saw Yong Joong yesterday
and suggested the four of us...

10
00:00:58,020 --> 00:00:59,160
get together for a meal.

11
00:01:02,030 --> 00:01:03,160
What did she say to you?

12
00:01:03,560 --> 00:01:04,630
Was she hurt?

13
00:01:04,930 --> 00:01:06,930
It's not as simple...

14
00:01:06,930 --> 00:01:08,000
as getting hurt or hurting someone.

15
00:01:08,070 --> 00:01:09,800
Stop beating around the bush.

16
00:01:11,370 --> 00:01:12,870
Get to the point with facts.

17
00:01:16,540 --> 00:01:17,540
The fact is,

18
00:01:18,410 --> 00:01:19,480
I'm staying out of it.

19
00:01:21,810 --> 00:01:23,180
We're still good, right?

20
00:01:33,890 --> 00:01:35,190
We didn't discuss anything in particular.

21
00:01:35,660 --> 00:01:36,830
I don't want to.

22
00:01:37,300 --> 00:01:38,430
Are you never going to see him again?

23
00:01:42,370 --> 00:01:43,740
(We're ready for the surgery.)

24
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:46,910
I'm not attending the wedding either.

25
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:48,070
All right.

26
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:55,850
She's an orphan, so you have to help her.

27
00:01:56,050 --> 00:01:58,080
Can't you hide Kim Jin Ju
in a hospital this big?

28
00:01:59,320 --> 00:02:01,620
And it'd be easy enough
to alter her appearance a bit.

29
00:02:20,470 --> 00:02:21,740
Two lattes, please.

30
00:02:35,190 --> 00:02:36,790
One Americano.

31
00:02:44,460 --> 00:02:45,460
Ready!

32
00:02:46,130 --> 00:02:47,130
Action!

33
00:02:52,610 --> 00:02:53,840
What do you think you're doing?

34
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:54,970
We're over!

35
00:03:10,390 --> 00:03:11,420
Cut!

36
00:03:11,420 --> 00:03:12,630
What are you doing? Get in!

37
00:03:13,060 --> 00:03:14,460
Excuse me! Wait!

38
00:03:14,530 --> 00:03:15,600
Hey, Momo!

39
00:03:20,870 --> 00:03:23,370
(Nua General Hospital)

40
00:03:27,810 --> 00:03:28,840
Are you uncomfortable?

41
00:03:36,020 --> 00:03:38,280
Hey, take me to Nua General Hospital.

42
00:03:39,250 --> 00:03:41,220
Nua General Hospital?
Are you feeling unwell?

43
00:03:44,090 --> 00:03:48,030
(Nua General Hospital, Neurology Center)

44
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:23,100
(Nua General Hospital)

45
00:04:48,050 --> 00:04:51,160
(Nua General Hospital)

46
00:05:14,210 --> 00:05:15,820
(Actress Momo)

47
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:16,880
I'm done.

48
00:05:19,420 --> 00:05:21,190
(Nua General Hospital)

49
00:05:54,350 --> 00:05:56,620
Are you not in, Mr. Kim?

50
00:05:58,120 --> 00:06:00,830
I'll tell you more once I find my child.

51
00:06:01,260 --> 00:06:02,830
It was CEO Hyun Ran Hee all along.

52
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:05,730
And they met again
because I bought a painting.

53
00:06:09,670 --> 00:06:13,570
I'd probably feel the same way about me
if I were you.

54
00:06:13,840 --> 00:06:14,840
Right?

55
00:06:16,010 --> 00:06:18,680
He's my brother,
but I raised him like my own son...

56
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:19,810
and took care of him.

57
00:06:20,580 --> 00:06:22,250
So frankly, I'm a little disappointed.

58
00:06:23,180 --> 00:06:24,320
But what can I do?

59
00:06:26,090 --> 00:06:27,490
I'll treat Yong Joong well.

60
00:06:29,390 --> 00:06:31,290
I heard you had an older sister.

61
00:06:31,660 --> 00:06:34,930
Was Paul Kim, the artist,
CEO Hyun's first love?

62
00:06:36,900 --> 00:06:37,900
Yes.

63
00:06:38,630 --> 00:06:42,030
I met him a couple of times
after my mother passed away.

64
00:06:42,270 --> 00:06:44,140
He was desperately searching
for his lost daughter.

65
00:06:44,470 --> 00:06:45,470
How about you?

66
00:06:47,510 --> 00:06:48,870
I'm asking if you want to meet her.

67
00:06:50,780 --> 00:06:54,080
Of course. You know I grew up lonely.

68
00:06:54,780 --> 00:06:56,380
But I think it's going to be hard.

69
00:06:56,980 --> 00:06:59,620
The restaurant owner who brought the baby
from Japan to Korea...

70
00:07:00,020 --> 00:07:01,890
could be raising the child herself.

71
00:07:02,860 --> 00:07:07,290
I hired a PI to look for Kim Jin Ju,
but he found a dead girl with that name.

72
00:07:13,470 --> 00:07:16,300
They say drinking cold stuff like that
can make it harder to get pregnant.

73
00:07:16,640 --> 00:07:18,300
That's what the director
at the Seonyeon Medical Clinic says.

74
00:07:19,170 --> 00:07:21,270
I might not let you see the baby
when it's born.

75
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:23,840
You'd better treat me right.

76
00:07:36,960 --> 00:07:38,690
When are you having your bridal shower?

77
00:07:43,060 --> 00:07:44,060
I'm not having one.

78
00:07:45,530 --> 00:07:48,330
I brought this for you.
It's Pickles' replacement.

79
00:07:51,270 --> 00:07:52,300
No, thanks.

80
00:07:52,770 --> 00:07:57,310
Susan, Ah Ri, Jin Ju Kyung,
Ma Yeon Su, and Bo Ra.

81
00:07:57,640 --> 00:07:58,940
They all came.

82
00:08:02,010 --> 00:08:04,880
You have to throw one.
It's a once-in-a-lifetime thing...

83
00:08:06,450 --> 00:08:07,750
It'll only happen once, right?

84
00:08:09,620 --> 00:08:11,760
You've had too much to drink.
Go on and get some rest.

85
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:15,390
I don't want to sober up.
I'm in such a good mood.

86
00:08:17,330 --> 00:08:18,360
I want to drink more.

87
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:21,970
Let's go to a karaoke bar.
We've never gone together.

88
00:08:23,100 --> 00:08:25,970
We've been four times already,
including the last time.

89
00:08:26,810 --> 00:08:28,740
We won't see each other
after I get married, right?

90
00:08:31,910 --> 00:08:33,010
This is how we're saying goodbye?

91
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:34,980
We should at least have a proper send-off.

92
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:38,220
- Manager Oh.
- Yes?

93
00:08:38,280 --> 00:08:39,890
- The Silro Hotel.
- Okay.

94
00:08:39,950 --> 00:08:41,690
I came out without my wallet.

95
00:08:42,490 --> 00:08:43,690
You think I'd make you pay?

96
00:08:54,130 --> 00:08:57,770
Imagine how bleak the world would be
without flowers.

97
00:08:58,900 --> 00:09:01,470
She never really liked flowers
that much...

98
00:09:04,210 --> 00:09:06,550
My future brother-in-law, James.

99
00:09:08,450 --> 00:09:10,520
Do you know any women
you could set him up with?

100
00:09:10,850 --> 00:09:12,320
Even a divorced reporter would do.

101
00:09:13,990 --> 00:09:15,120
You don't want to answer?

102
00:09:16,090 --> 00:09:17,490
Just rest on the way.

103
00:09:17,490 --> 00:09:19,390
This is how I rest, by chatting.

104
00:09:21,790 --> 00:09:23,060
Is it just me?

105
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:25,400
You look like you're looking down on me.

106
00:09:27,330 --> 00:09:29,100
Why would I look down on you, Momo?

107
00:09:29,100 --> 00:09:30,800
When you marry Ju Shin,

108
00:09:31,570 --> 00:09:33,540
are you going to start calling me
your sister-in-law?

109
00:09:39,040 --> 00:09:42,850
Honestly, you don't even like him.
You're just going through with it, right?

110
00:09:45,020 --> 00:09:46,020
I've grown to like him.

111
00:09:46,690 --> 00:09:49,020
What is there to like? Like what?

112
00:09:49,590 --> 00:09:50,720
He has his charms.

113
00:09:52,830 --> 00:09:55,090
And how long do you think
that charm will last?

114
00:09:55,860 --> 00:09:57,300
Happiness isn't easy.

115
00:09:58,130 --> 00:09:59,230
You have to work at it.

116
00:10:00,830 --> 00:10:02,530
You think I didn't try?

117
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:10,480
Hello?

118
00:10:12,180 --> 00:10:13,280
Oh my, when?

119
00:10:14,610 --> 00:10:15,880
I didn't know.

120
00:10:15,880 --> 00:10:18,180
I'm Kim Jin Ju.

121
00:10:18,250 --> 00:10:19,720
Well, congratulations.

122
00:10:20,650 --> 00:10:21,650
Yes.

123
00:10:21,990 --> 00:10:23,260
I'll check my schedule.

124
00:10:24,290 --> 00:10:25,290
Okay.

125
00:10:36,170 --> 00:10:38,870
Your mom wouldn't let you get a cat
when you wanted one, remember?

126
00:10:39,170 --> 00:10:40,670
She hated how they shed.

127
00:10:40,740 --> 00:10:41,910
Was that it?

128
00:10:44,940 --> 00:10:46,650
Do you ever think about Kim Jin Ju?

129
00:10:51,280 --> 00:10:52,580
You don't? Not at all?

130
00:10:53,220 --> 00:10:54,590
How could I not?

131
00:10:55,890 --> 00:10:56,890
Why?

132
00:10:57,420 --> 00:10:58,960
She just pops into my head now and then.

133
00:11:00,830 --> 00:11:02,260
What do you think about?

134
00:11:02,390 --> 00:11:04,060
Good memories? Bad ones?

135
00:11:08,030 --> 00:11:10,540
Kim Jin Ju used to talk about you a lot.

136
00:11:11,340 --> 00:11:13,870
She said you both relied on each other
to get through your time at the orphanage.

137
00:11:22,180 --> 00:11:23,550
That heartless tramp.

138
00:11:24,050 --> 00:11:25,180
You said you wanted to sing, didn't you?

139
00:11:26,420 --> 00:11:27,420
Any requests?

140
00:11:27,950 --> 00:11:29,960
Just sing whatever you want.

141
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:31,220
What did I sing last time?

142
00:11:32,830 --> 00:11:33,960
How would I know?

143
00:11:35,060 --> 00:11:36,130
You don't remember?

144
00:11:38,830 --> 00:11:41,100
Of course I do.
It's my go-to karaoke song.

145
00:11:43,970 --> 00:11:44,970
But today...

146
00:11:47,670 --> 00:11:49,440
(My Love is Far Away)

147
00:12:03,420 --> 00:12:08,230
I should have told you

148
00:12:10,260 --> 00:12:16,300
That I loved you

149
00:12:18,040 --> 00:12:23,010
That without you

150
00:12:24,880 --> 00:12:30,550
I can't live on

151
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:37,660
I should have told you

152
00:12:39,460 --> 00:12:45,200
That I loved you

153
00:12:47,230 --> 00:12:52,570
But I hesitated

154
00:12:54,470 --> 00:12:59,710
And my love is gone

155
00:13:03,020 --> 00:13:06,190
I gave you my heart

156
00:13:10,220 --> 00:13:13,790
I gave you my tears

157
00:13:17,460 --> 00:13:21,600
And I gave you my dreams

158
00:13:24,070 --> 00:13:28,740
But you drifted away

159
00:13:30,440 --> 00:13:35,410
My love is far away

160
00:13:37,420 --> 00:13:42,590
Forever far away

161
00:13:45,090 --> 00:13:50,100
But I hesitated

162
00:13:52,230 --> 00:13:57,140
And my love is gone

163
00:14:17,820 --> 00:14:19,060
You try getting hit.

164
00:14:19,190 --> 00:14:20,730
You know what that's like,
the humiliation.

165
00:14:21,430 --> 00:14:22,660
I never said that.

166
00:14:24,030 --> 00:14:26,000
You did. Some time ago.

167
00:14:36,210 --> 00:14:37,210
Hey.

168
00:14:37,640 --> 00:14:40,110
- I guess I'm not that girly.
- Why?

169
00:14:40,110 --> 00:14:41,750
I just don't get the big deal
about flowers.

170
00:14:42,250 --> 00:14:43,280
Really?

171
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:45,150
Maybe it's because I get them so often?

172
00:14:46,390 --> 00:14:48,850
No. I've just always been like that.

173
00:14:49,050 --> 00:14:50,690
They just don't do anything for me.

174
00:14:51,090 --> 00:14:53,690
(Jaeil Apartments)

175
00:14:54,730 --> 00:14:56,960
First floor. The doors are closing.

176
00:15:00,930 --> 00:15:02,700
Hey, you take the cat.

177
00:15:03,300 --> 00:15:04,300
Okay.

178
00:15:16,650 --> 00:15:17,650
(Director Shin Ju Shin)

179
00:15:25,120 --> 00:15:26,260
In the dead of night,

180
00:15:27,590 --> 00:15:29,160
you're not exactly dressed for a walk.

181
00:15:29,900 --> 00:15:31,130
I was coming to see you.

182
00:15:32,260 --> 00:15:33,430
What brings you here?

183
00:15:33,430 --> 00:15:34,600
There's something I need to talk about.

184
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:36,640
Is there a good place to talk nearby?

185
00:15:38,040 --> 00:15:39,370
Why don't you come up for a minute?

186
00:15:41,810 --> 00:15:42,840
No.

187
00:15:43,410 --> 00:15:44,410
Some other time.

188
00:15:51,350 --> 00:15:52,420
Is something wrong?

189
00:15:54,920 --> 00:15:55,920
Momo.

190
00:15:57,320 --> 00:15:58,920
Haven't you noticed anything strange
about her?

191
00:16:02,960 --> 00:16:04,060
It seems like...

192
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:06,930
she's possessed.

193
00:16:07,900 --> 00:16:09,130
I'm almost certain.

194
00:16:13,240 --> 00:16:15,610
- About that matter...
- So you've noticed it too?

195
00:16:18,040 --> 00:16:19,040
If...

196
00:16:21,310 --> 00:16:22,810
you could become Momo...

197
00:16:24,250 --> 00:16:25,480
without Yong Joong knowing...

198
00:16:29,120 --> 00:16:30,490
This might be your last chance...

199
00:16:31,560 --> 00:16:32,760
to become Momo...

200
00:16:33,360 --> 00:16:34,860
and marry Yong Joong.

201
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:40,800
You're not the joking type.

202
00:16:41,330 --> 00:16:42,430
I'm not joking.

203
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:45,070
I'm saying I can make it happen
if you want.

204
00:16:47,470 --> 00:16:48,470
There is a way.

205
00:16:53,080 --> 00:16:54,280
She's not possessed.

206
00:16:59,480 --> 00:17:00,690
It really is Kim Jin Ju.

207
00:17:07,160 --> 00:17:08,560
What do you mean?

208
00:17:11,800 --> 00:17:12,900
How?

209
00:17:16,270 --> 00:17:17,340
A brain swap.

210
00:17:25,940 --> 00:17:28,510
She only looks like Momo. Just the body.

211
00:17:32,780 --> 00:17:34,350
First, it was Momo's mom, CEO Hyun.

212
00:17:35,390 --> 00:17:36,420
And then Kim Jin Ju.

213
00:17:39,090 --> 00:17:40,330
It's hard to believe,

214
00:17:41,890 --> 00:17:43,030
but I'm the one who did the surgery.

215
00:17:43,430 --> 00:17:44,500
How can you...

216
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:49,070
swap brains?

217
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:52,870
Remember last time I said
I could be world-renowned if I wanted to?

218
00:17:54,210 --> 00:17:55,340
My late father,

219
00:17:57,540 --> 00:17:59,610
Momo's mom, Kim Jin Ju,

220
00:18:00,750 --> 00:18:02,680
Lee Shim, and Nurse Park Soo
are the only ones who know.

221
00:18:04,820 --> 00:18:05,820
Why?

222
00:18:07,420 --> 00:18:08,550
Momo's brain...

223
00:18:10,520 --> 00:18:11,620
was too...

224
00:18:12,260 --> 00:18:13,390
damaged...

225
00:18:14,890 --> 00:18:16,230
from the diving accident back then.

226
00:18:19,260 --> 00:18:21,630
Momo's mom said it was the only way.

227
00:18:24,700 --> 00:18:26,510
I thought Jin Ju had really died,

228
00:18:28,670 --> 00:18:31,040
so I thought her spirit possessed Momo.

229
00:18:34,250 --> 00:18:36,680
Still, you'd have to be a fool
not to notice.

230
00:18:36,950 --> 00:18:40,590
Especially since even I, Kim Jin Ju,
have won over Ha Yong Joong.

231
00:18:40,650 --> 00:18:43,050
How are you going to live with yourself,
Geum Ba Ra?

232
00:18:54,630 --> 00:18:56,370
Life is worth living.

233
00:18:57,300 --> 00:18:59,370
Even when you're at rock bottom.

234
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:05,140
Should I just come out and say
I'm Kim Jin Ju?

235
00:19:07,710 --> 00:19:09,250
If you want, I can swap your brain.

236
00:19:10,980 --> 00:19:12,120
Then what happens to Jin Ju?

237
00:19:17,990 --> 00:19:19,620
No, I don't want her taking over my body.

238
00:19:21,830 --> 00:19:22,830
I refuse.

239
00:19:24,730 --> 00:19:27,300
You should've let me see Momo once
before her surgery.

240
00:19:29,230 --> 00:19:30,470
You were better off not seeing her.

241
00:19:31,240 --> 00:19:32,500
Was it that bad?

242
00:19:38,510 --> 00:19:39,740
Anyway, think about it.

243
00:19:47,150 --> 00:19:48,920
Now that I think about it,
it's not me you're doing this for, is it?

244
00:19:52,920 --> 00:19:54,190
Just follow your heart.

245
00:19:55,190 --> 00:19:56,460
Your true feelings.

246
00:19:58,200 --> 00:19:59,530
It doesn't matter to me.

247
00:20:02,930 --> 00:20:04,900
Do all women look this beautiful
under the moonlight?

248
00:20:14,210 --> 00:20:15,780
Just like last time in my garden.

249
00:20:21,190 --> 00:20:22,190
To be honest...

250
00:20:24,220 --> 00:20:26,190
I only made that offer
hoping you'd say no.

251
00:20:28,460 --> 00:20:30,900
My conscience keeps nagging at me,

252
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:33,130
but I just can't seem to ignore it.

253
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:39,770
Didn't you say you've been holding on
because of Ha Yong Joong?

254
00:20:41,640 --> 00:20:42,740
To me, you...

255
00:20:44,840 --> 00:20:45,940
are not nearly that serious.

256
00:20:49,650 --> 00:20:50,650
Change...

257
00:20:55,320 --> 00:20:56,320
Okay?

258
00:21:09,630 --> 00:21:11,200
I guess the body is meaningless.

259
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:15,340
She really wasn't the Momo I used to know.

260
00:21:17,480 --> 00:21:20,510
I guess everyone is born
with their own disposition.

261
00:21:22,610 --> 00:21:23,620
What about the baby?

262
00:21:25,780 --> 00:21:27,550
She got pregnant before Jin Ju's surgery.

263
00:21:30,690 --> 00:21:32,420
This is a little awkward.

264
00:21:35,030 --> 00:21:36,660
This is the last thing I can do for you.

265
00:21:37,730 --> 00:21:39,730
My feelings for you haven't changed.

266
00:21:40,570 --> 00:21:41,970
There was nothing to change
in the first place.

267
00:21:43,800 --> 00:21:45,070
We never even dated.

268
00:21:51,610 --> 00:21:52,680
What do you think of my name?

269
00:21:57,620 --> 00:21:58,620
I...

270
00:21:59,950 --> 00:22:01,450
don't like the "Shin" part of it.

271
00:22:03,620 --> 00:22:04,890
Although the characters are different,

272
00:22:05,260 --> 00:22:07,030
it keeps making me think
of the "Shin" for "ghost."

273
00:22:30,920 --> 00:22:32,680
I've succeeded both times,

274
00:22:33,750 --> 00:22:35,020
so don't you worry.

275
00:23:52,330 --> 00:23:55,770
Turns out it wasn't temporary kleptomania
she had during her period.

276
00:23:55,770 --> 00:23:56,870
It was out of habit.

277
00:23:56,870 --> 00:23:59,700
So how could
we keep living together as a family?

278
00:24:00,870 --> 00:24:03,370
It would cause problems
for him eventually.

279
00:24:04,740 --> 00:24:07,380
I'm so sorry that I can barely face you.

280
00:24:07,750 --> 00:24:09,050
I'm speechless.

281
00:24:09,580 --> 00:24:11,250
I'm just glad...

282
00:24:12,150 --> 00:24:14,990
- it's been cleared up now.
- Watch out for Jin Ju.

283
00:24:16,020 --> 00:24:18,820
If she has betrayed you once,
she's bound to do it again.

284
00:24:39,640 --> 00:24:40,650
Momo...

285
00:24:42,910 --> 00:24:43,920
It's so true.

286
00:24:45,680 --> 00:24:47,890
You would never do that to me.

287
00:24:54,030 --> 00:24:55,060
Congratulations!

288
00:25:00,030 --> 00:25:01,430
- Congratulations!
- Congratulations!

289
00:25:32,030 --> 00:25:33,260
Although we're not blood-related,

290
00:25:33,260 --> 00:25:36,330
my cousin in Germany was very sick,
so I went for a visit.

291
00:25:36,530 --> 00:25:38,070
I see.

292
00:25:38,540 --> 00:25:41,640
I was worried something was wrong,
so I dropped by your house in Yangpyeong.

293
00:25:44,480 --> 00:25:46,080
Say hello. This is the artist, Paul Kim.

294
00:25:46,580 --> 00:25:48,880
- This is Manager Yoon.
- It's a pleasure to meet you.

295
00:25:51,320 --> 00:25:53,790
Our CEO is a great admirer of your work.

296
00:26:10,100 --> 00:26:11,440
I heard from Momo...

297
00:26:12,100 --> 00:26:14,270
that the birth mother of the daughter
you're looking for is CEO Hyun.

298
00:26:17,140 --> 00:26:18,980
It's a small world, isn't it?

299
00:26:20,210 --> 00:26:21,750
Have you been invited to the wedding?

300
00:26:23,450 --> 00:26:25,880
- Not yet.
- We'd be happy to invite you.

301
00:26:27,020 --> 00:26:28,020
To be honest,

302
00:26:28,350 --> 00:26:30,790
since she was engaged
to Director Shin Ju Shin,

303
00:26:31,120 --> 00:26:32,790
it was a bit awkward from my end.

304
00:26:32,990 --> 00:26:35,460
I don't know how you'll take this, but...

305
00:26:36,390 --> 00:26:37,600
Don't worry about me.

306
00:26:40,060 --> 00:26:41,130
That's perfectly understandable.

307
00:26:43,270 --> 00:26:45,170
The officer in charge of the case
back then said...

308
00:26:45,870 --> 00:26:48,140
that the person on the CCTV
looked like a total pro.

309
00:26:48,740 --> 00:26:52,780
Thanks to this man,
Jin Ju barely avoided juvie.

310
00:26:54,650 --> 00:26:57,750
Jin Ju's been secretly reading your diary.

311
00:26:57,950 --> 00:26:59,180
She did it again last night.

312
00:27:00,180 --> 00:27:02,090
Promise you won't tell her
you heard it from me.

313
00:27:09,560 --> 00:27:10,600
You scared me.

314
00:27:16,170 --> 00:27:17,200
When did you get here?

315
00:27:20,610 --> 00:27:21,910
Let me go get changed.

316
00:27:28,680 --> 00:27:30,620
She's figured it out, hasn't she?

317
00:27:36,450 --> 00:27:37,720
Why are you staring at me like that?

318
00:27:41,360 --> 00:27:42,390
Are you Kim Jin Ju?

319
00:27:50,970 --> 00:27:52,670
Kim Gwang Cheol was right.

320
00:27:53,770 --> 00:27:55,410
He said you'd never take your life.

321
00:27:55,410 --> 00:27:56,840
What's your point?

322
00:27:57,240 --> 00:27:58,310
I'll pretend I don't know.

323
00:27:59,210 --> 00:28:00,480
But leave Yong Joong alone.

324
00:28:03,110 --> 00:28:04,280
You can easily find...

325
00:28:05,150 --> 00:28:06,850
someone so much better.

326
00:28:07,320 --> 00:28:08,350
No.

327
00:28:08,690 --> 00:28:10,350
I like Yong Joong too, you know.

328
00:28:10,660 --> 00:28:12,620
- A lot.
- Since when?

329
00:28:12,920 --> 00:28:14,960
- Even if the whole world is...
- If I tell him,

330
00:28:15,230 --> 00:28:16,760
will he still like you?

331
00:28:18,300 --> 00:28:21,230
It's the soul that matters, not the body.

332
00:28:22,100 --> 00:28:25,170
The brain is just a chunk of protein.

333
00:28:27,870 --> 00:28:31,380
Tell him. If he doesn't believe you,
I'll show him the surgical scar.

334
00:28:32,180 --> 00:28:33,180
Want to see it?

335
00:28:33,750 --> 00:28:34,750
Forget it.

336
00:28:35,350 --> 00:28:36,880
If I tell the whole world...

337
00:28:37,550 --> 00:28:40,380
that Director Shin Ju Shin of Nua Hospital
performed a brain swap...

338
00:28:41,390 --> 00:28:43,420
Even if there have been head transplants,

339
00:28:43,420 --> 00:28:45,220
wouldn't a brain-only transplant
be a world first?

340
00:28:48,930 --> 00:28:51,130
People would absolutely lose their minds.

341
00:28:54,100 --> 00:28:55,200
And then what happens?

342
00:28:56,270 --> 00:28:58,570
He'd get a few years for murder,
wouldn't he?

343
00:28:59,440 --> 00:29:01,370
CEO Hyun, Kim Jin Ju...

344
00:29:03,840 --> 00:29:06,680
Momo's mom has a place in a columbarium,
so we can just say she killed herself.

345
00:29:09,150 --> 00:29:10,310
But what about me? Kim Jin Ju?

346
00:29:12,520 --> 00:29:14,950
I don't even know
how they disposed of my body.

347
00:29:16,850 --> 00:29:18,060
I can't even ask them.

348
00:29:22,390 --> 00:29:23,660
Forget a grave,

349
00:29:24,260 --> 00:29:25,800
I vanished without a trace...

350
00:29:27,030 --> 00:29:28,070
from this world.

351
00:29:32,370 --> 00:29:35,140
You just can't stand to see me succeed,
can you?

352
00:29:36,910 --> 00:29:39,210
You should have just married
Director Shin.

353
00:29:40,210 --> 00:29:42,150
You loved him more than anyone.

354
00:29:42,210 --> 00:29:45,050
And you loved Ha Yong Joong
more than anyone.

355
00:29:47,390 --> 00:29:51,320
- After everything I've done for you...
- What about what I've done for you!

356
00:29:51,390 --> 00:29:53,360
- Should I spell it out for you?
- Go on!

357
00:29:56,190 --> 00:29:59,160
If I cross Attorney Tae Won Young,
he might retaliate.

358
00:29:59,600 --> 00:30:01,070
Not as a friend,

359
00:30:01,600 --> 00:30:03,870
I looked after you
like my own little sister.

360
00:30:06,370 --> 00:30:08,370
How can you say that so casually?

361
00:30:08,440 --> 00:30:10,510
I don't want to bring up that awful past.

362
00:30:10,640 --> 00:30:11,740
So, what's it going to be?

363
00:30:12,040 --> 00:30:13,810
Shall we go to the police station together
right now?

364
00:30:14,380 --> 00:30:16,550
Expose it all? To the whole world?

365
00:30:20,690 --> 00:30:24,360
I get why you like Yong Joong.

366
00:30:24,890 --> 00:30:26,720
He's just so, so sweet.

367
00:30:27,260 --> 00:30:29,090
He's completely different
from Director Shin.

368
00:30:30,900 --> 00:30:33,360
We're both starving for affection,
aren't we?

369
00:30:36,670 --> 00:30:39,400
All that pain
that's seared into our souls,

370
00:30:40,300 --> 00:30:41,810
a lot of it has already melted away.

371
00:30:48,150 --> 00:30:50,280
Just looking at Ha Yong Joong
makes me feel good,

372
00:30:51,380 --> 00:30:52,950
but you know that better than anyone.

373
00:30:58,790 --> 00:30:59,990
I feel so free.

374
00:31:00,760 --> 00:31:03,160
Now there's nothing left to hide,
is there?

375
00:31:03,790 --> 00:31:06,660
Secrets are surprisingly exhausting,
you know?

376
00:31:08,200 --> 00:31:10,300
We've both made it to the upper class now.

377
00:31:11,040 --> 00:31:14,410
You'll get to wear all the designer brands
you want now, right?

378
00:31:15,210 --> 00:31:18,040
As the wife of Nua Hospital's director
and its foundation.

379
00:31:19,140 --> 00:31:20,810
Aren't you afraid of divine judgment?

380
00:31:21,250 --> 00:31:23,610
Why would I? What's there to be afraid of?

381
00:31:23,780 --> 00:31:26,280
It's not like I was the one
who swapped our brains.

382
00:31:27,450 --> 00:31:30,350
The one who should be terrified
is Director Shin.

383
00:31:33,420 --> 00:31:34,830
What were you thinking,
spilling the beans?

384
00:31:34,830 --> 00:31:36,360
Did you confirm it with Director Shin?

385
00:31:40,400 --> 00:31:43,200
I admit, I was dying to tell someone.

386
00:31:44,570 --> 00:31:46,400
I was curious to see
how the world would react.

387
00:31:51,810 --> 00:31:53,510
You don't want to mess with me.

388
00:31:57,080 --> 00:31:58,820
And here I was, about to wish you well.

389
00:32:01,950 --> 00:32:03,120
Time to change my number.

390
00:32:11,630 --> 00:32:13,360
I hope I never have to see
your face again.

391
00:32:30,180 --> 00:32:33,750
Alright. Shoulder, 19 and a half.

392
00:32:51,570 --> 00:32:52,940
(Nua General Hospital)

393
00:32:58,910 --> 00:33:00,040
Are you not feeling well?

394
00:33:00,750 --> 00:33:01,810
No.

395
00:33:01,810 --> 00:33:02,880
Then,

396
00:33:03,480 --> 00:33:04,880
are you here to see Director Shin?

397
00:33:05,320 --> 00:33:06,850
I didn't get to see him.

398
00:33:08,090 --> 00:33:10,050
Let's have a cup of tea at the cafe here.

399
00:33:12,690 --> 00:33:15,460
I'm helping people park without pay.

400
00:33:23,200 --> 00:33:25,070
What's Director Shin like?

401
00:33:29,140 --> 00:33:31,510
Did he visit the orphanage
from time to time?

402
00:33:32,080 --> 00:33:33,410
Yes, a few times.

403
00:33:35,550 --> 00:33:36,750
Do you still...

404
00:33:38,320 --> 00:33:40,350
think that Jin Ju is still alive?

405
00:33:40,790 --> 00:33:42,220
Of course, I do.

406
00:33:42,650 --> 00:33:45,720
You're a reporter,
so think about it logically.

407
00:33:45,820 --> 00:33:47,760
If she really intended to kill herself,

408
00:33:47,890 --> 00:33:51,030
she would've jumped in the water
right in front of a CCTV camera.

409
00:33:52,330 --> 00:33:55,400
To make a big show of it
for the whole world to see.

410
00:33:59,040 --> 00:34:01,670
How long does she think
she can stay hidden?

411
00:34:04,810 --> 00:34:07,310
Have any relatives come looking
for you yet?

412
00:34:08,580 --> 00:34:09,750
No.

413
00:34:09,750 --> 00:34:12,820
I bet a shaman could tell us.

414
00:34:13,050 --> 00:34:15,990
But we don't know your date of birth,
so it's no use.

415
00:34:16,620 --> 00:34:19,420
Wasn't there some kind of note?
With your birth date and time on it.

416
00:34:22,130 --> 00:34:23,530
This is just hypothetical,

417
00:34:26,530 --> 00:34:29,730
- but if Jin Ju were really alive...
- Tell me what you know!

418
00:34:29,970 --> 00:34:31,440
- I don't...
- You know something!

419
00:34:31,740 --> 00:34:32,740
It's just that...

420
00:34:33,670 --> 00:34:35,940
I'm just curious why you can't seem
to give up on her.

421
00:34:36,440 --> 00:34:38,040
How could I give up on my own child?

422
00:34:38,380 --> 00:34:40,440
That's just how a parent's love is.

423
00:34:41,180 --> 00:34:43,580
But since I'm such a pathetic father...

424
00:34:45,020 --> 00:34:47,080
Imagine if I'd shown up as a rich dad.

425
00:34:48,590 --> 00:34:51,020
Do you think she would've just vanished
like she was dead?

426
00:34:51,890 --> 00:34:54,360
If you know anything at all,
please let me know.

427
00:34:55,790 --> 00:35:00,300
I'm sure of it.
Momo or Director Shin is hiding her.

428
00:35:02,800 --> 00:35:04,370
Why would Director Shin...

429
00:35:04,770 --> 00:35:07,610
He's extremely busy.
He wouldn't have time or energy for that.

430
00:35:07,670 --> 00:35:10,170
Because she came from his orphanage.

431
00:35:38,900 --> 00:35:42,040
The phone is turned off.
Please leave a message after the tone.

432
00:35:43,470 --> 00:35:45,340
Chairman Shin sits at the head table.

433
00:35:47,010 --> 00:35:48,450
And Yoon Su Hyun can sit wherever.

434
00:35:50,580 --> 00:35:52,020
Geum Ba Ra isn't coming.

435
00:35:53,480 --> 00:35:55,020
Do I have to explain everything?

436
00:36:02,230 --> 00:36:03,360
(Geum Ba Ra)

437
00:36:03,430 --> 00:36:05,930
(I enjoyed dinner. Thank...)

438
00:36:08,870 --> 00:36:12,740
(Dinner was delicious...)

439
00:36:16,470 --> 00:36:19,040
- Hello, Mr. Kim.
- Hello.

440
00:36:19,110 --> 00:36:20,880
Are you driving tomorrow?

441
00:36:22,010 --> 00:36:23,980
- To the wedding hall?
- Yes.

442
00:36:24,050 --> 00:36:25,920
I didn't get an invitation.

443
00:36:26,420 --> 00:36:27,420
Really?

444
00:36:27,420 --> 00:36:30,350
I understand. The press will be there,

445
00:36:30,420 --> 00:36:32,960
and it could start rumors
if we're not careful.

446
00:36:33,090 --> 00:36:35,790
Come on, we didn't say anything.
What kind of rumors?

447
00:36:35,930 --> 00:36:38,160
I was even wondering if you'd be walking
the bride down the aisle.

448
00:36:49,070 --> 00:36:50,310
(Geum Ba Ra)

449
00:37:03,150 --> 00:37:04,620
The number you have dialed...

450
00:37:04,620 --> 00:37:09,090
has been temporarily suspended
at the customer’s request.

451
00:37:20,240 --> 00:37:22,110
- Where's Momo?
- The restroom.

452
00:37:23,070 --> 00:37:25,110
- You're here.
- Did you sleep well?

453
00:37:25,110 --> 00:37:26,140
Yes.

454
00:37:26,780 --> 00:37:29,010
James, you should get a little
makeup done too.

455
00:37:29,180 --> 00:37:31,680
If I wear makeup, I'll outshine the groom.

456
00:37:32,950 --> 00:37:35,320
- Sir, some coffee...
- I already had some, thanks.

457
00:37:36,150 --> 00:37:38,190
Is Reporter Geum at my table?

458
00:37:38,820 --> 00:37:39,960
I don't know.

459
00:37:40,960 --> 00:37:42,130
She's probably not coming.

460
00:37:42,560 --> 00:37:44,530
Why isn't she coming? Of all people.

461
00:37:45,430 --> 00:37:47,430
I guess she felt awkward coming alone.

462
00:37:48,400 --> 00:37:50,600
I heard Paul wasn't invited either.

463
00:37:50,800 --> 00:37:52,840
Our guest list was just too long.

464
00:37:53,300 --> 00:37:55,140
So you're walking in alone?

465
00:37:56,440 --> 00:37:57,470
Together.

466
00:37:59,880 --> 00:38:04,720
We will shortly begin the wedding ceremony
for Ha Yong Joong and Momo.

467
00:38:04,780 --> 00:38:07,120
Would our guests please
make their way inside...

468
00:38:07,180 --> 00:38:09,820
and take their seats? Thank you.

469
00:38:09,890 --> 00:38:11,560
(It looks like no one's home.)

470
00:38:11,620 --> 00:38:14,360
The bride and groom will now
make their entrance together.

471
00:38:14,490 --> 00:38:16,990
Please give them a warm round of applause!

472
00:38:46,120 --> 00:38:47,160
Thank you.

473
00:40:15,480 --> 00:40:17,150
You know how in foreign movies,

474
00:40:17,450 --> 00:40:20,320
brides do a father-daughter dance
at the wedding.

475
00:40:21,050 --> 00:40:24,250
But no matter how many times I marry,
I won't have a dad to dance with.

476
00:40:25,560 --> 00:40:27,290
But I still wanted to learn how.

477
00:41:27,890 --> 00:41:28,890
Are you nervous?

478
00:41:29,450 --> 00:41:31,990
- No.
- Let's be less formal.

479
00:41:32,260 --> 00:41:33,520
We're married now.

480
00:42:08,190 --> 00:42:09,890
What's taking him so long?

481
00:42:12,430 --> 00:42:15,900
Every time I hear this music,
I always think...

482
00:42:18,100 --> 00:42:19,100
About me?

483
00:42:21,770 --> 00:42:24,310
What? Is there a story behind this song?

484
00:42:27,310 --> 00:42:29,310
My memory is really spotty.

485
00:42:29,450 --> 00:42:31,680
I just can't remember parts of things...

486
00:42:32,050 --> 00:42:33,980
that happened with people.

487
00:42:36,650 --> 00:42:38,160
It doesn't matter if you've forgotten.

488
00:42:45,900 --> 00:42:48,530
Are you bummed that Ba Ra
didn't come today?

489
00:42:55,240 --> 00:42:56,240
Call her.

490
00:42:56,740 --> 00:42:58,780
This should get under Ba Ra's skin.

491
00:43:01,710 --> 00:43:02,750
A video call.

492
00:43:11,990 --> 00:43:12,990
Are you tired?

493
00:43:13,320 --> 00:43:14,420
Are you?

494
00:43:17,890 --> 00:43:18,960
Let's be honest.

495
00:43:19,630 --> 00:43:21,300
We postponed our trip...

496
00:43:21,930 --> 00:43:24,570
for Ba Ra's wedding
and not because of work, right?

497
00:43:25,940 --> 00:43:27,900
If we're going to go,
we should plan it right.

498
00:43:28,440 --> 00:43:30,940
That way, we can make the most of our trip
since we rarely get to go.

499
00:43:31,070 --> 00:43:33,610
Wouldn't we be doing each other a favor
by not attending each other's weddings?

500
00:43:35,050 --> 00:43:37,650
It's meaningless unless
you're genuinely happy for them, right?

501
00:43:38,450 --> 00:43:41,350
James will go to represent
our family anyway.

502
00:43:42,590 --> 00:43:43,590
We'll see.

503
00:43:46,190 --> 00:43:47,220
I'm going to go wash up.

504
00:44:47,520 --> 00:44:48,950
The number you have dialed...

505
00:44:48,950 --> 00:44:51,190
has been temporarily suspended
at the customer's request.

506
00:45:18,950 --> 00:45:22,720
It was great,
but I feel like something was missing.

507
00:45:23,620 --> 00:45:24,620
What was it?

508
00:45:26,390 --> 00:45:28,560
I wonder how Ba Ra is feeling right now.

509
00:45:48,010 --> 00:45:50,610
(This is Geum Ba Ra. Director Shin,
I'm writing this with a heavy heart.)

510
00:45:53,020 --> 00:45:54,150
This is Geum Ba Ra.

511
00:45:55,320 --> 00:45:56,320
Director Shin,

512
00:45:57,220 --> 00:45:59,820
I'm writing this with a heavy heart.

513
00:46:01,120 --> 00:46:04,160
Due to my insecurities and shortcomings,
I couldn't face you in person,

514
00:46:04,900 --> 00:46:07,460
so please forgive me for saying
goodbye this way.

515
00:46:08,300 --> 00:46:12,570
In every way, I fall short
and am not worthy of you.

516
00:46:13,170 --> 00:46:17,610
I truly hope you meet someone wonderful
who is worthy of you,

517
00:46:17,870 --> 00:46:19,980
build a beautiful family,
and find happiness.

518
00:46:20,280 --> 00:46:22,550
I'll be praying for you with all my heart
from afar.

519
00:46:24,280 --> 00:46:27,080
I will never forget your kindness
and all you've done for me...

520
00:46:27,750 --> 00:46:29,550
for as long as I live,

521
00:46:30,090 --> 00:46:32,190
and I promise to repay you someday.

522
00:46:32,890 --> 00:46:35,290
Please take care of yourself and be well.

523
00:46:36,760 --> 00:46:37,760
Geum Ba Ra.

524
00:47:04,250 --> 00:47:07,190
I'll be honest, I'm not much of a cook.
I'll learn as I go.

525
00:47:07,590 --> 00:47:08,890
I barely eat breakfast anyway.

526
00:47:09,360 --> 00:47:11,090
Just some milk or coffee after my run.

527
00:47:11,460 --> 00:47:13,460
Besides, the meal kits these days
are so good.

528
00:47:14,100 --> 00:47:15,570
James will keep sending us side dishes.

529
00:47:15,570 --> 00:47:16,600
(James)

530
00:47:17,730 --> 00:47:18,740
Telepathy.

531
00:47:20,900 --> 00:47:23,310
- Hey, James.
- Where did Reporter Geum take off to now?

532
00:47:25,240 --> 00:47:27,940
- Why?
- She missed the wedding yesterday,

533
00:47:28,680 --> 00:47:31,550
so I got worried and texted her
to have lunch,

534
00:47:31,550 --> 00:47:32,650
but she hasn't replied.

535
00:47:32,850 --> 00:47:34,120
My texts aren't even going through.

536
00:47:34,380 --> 00:47:37,850
I called, and it says her line
has been suspended at her request.

537
00:47:42,060 --> 00:47:43,330
You haven't heard anything?

538
00:47:44,030 --> 00:47:45,300
I'll ask Ju Shin.

539
00:47:46,460 --> 00:47:47,460
Okay.

540
00:47:56,540 --> 00:47:58,540
- Hello?
- James says...

541
00:47:58,540 --> 00:48:00,010
Ba Ra's phone has been suspended.

542
00:48:00,840 --> 00:48:01,850
I know.

543
00:48:02,250 --> 00:48:04,280
Did she just take off on a trip by herself
right before the wedding?

544
00:48:06,150 --> 00:48:07,150
No.

545
00:48:08,350 --> 00:48:09,350
Did you two fight?

546
00:48:13,260 --> 00:48:14,260
Why?

547
00:48:19,230 --> 00:48:20,230
She's gone.

548
00:48:23,300 --> 00:48:25,200
- Where to?
- I don't know.

549
00:48:27,870 --> 00:48:28,870
She just disappeared.

550
00:48:30,470 --> 00:48:31,640
What do you mean, disappeared?

551
00:48:32,810 --> 00:48:34,310
- I'm hanging up.
- Wait.

552
00:48:48,390 --> 00:48:49,390
What did the email say?

553
00:48:54,100 --> 00:48:55,670
(This is Geum Ba Ra. Director Shin,
I'm writing this with a heavy heart.)

554
00:49:05,780 --> 00:49:08,080
She would never give up
on marrying Director Shin.

555
00:49:09,250 --> 00:49:10,950
She must have some other plan.

556
00:49:21,830 --> 00:49:23,060
It's not what you're thinking...

557
00:49:25,430 --> 00:49:26,860
Nothing happened between Ba Ra and me.

558
00:49:29,570 --> 00:49:33,040
She stayed at my place for a few days,
in the guest room.

559
00:49:36,770 --> 00:49:38,040
If I'd known it would turn out like this,

560
00:49:39,310 --> 00:49:42,210
I wonder if I should've just left things
as they were.

561
00:49:45,520 --> 00:49:46,520
What does Momo say?

562
00:49:48,420 --> 00:49:49,820
She said she'd turn up eventually,

563
00:49:50,890 --> 00:49:52,090
like last time.

564
00:49:58,030 --> 00:49:59,460
You were everything...

565
00:50:00,630 --> 00:50:01,630
to Ba Ra.

566
00:50:05,940 --> 00:50:08,410
She told me you were her everything.

567
00:50:11,010 --> 00:50:12,040
Why are you telling me this now?

568
00:50:13,210 --> 00:50:14,210
You seriously didn't know?

569
00:50:18,850 --> 00:50:20,250
You're not that dense.

570
00:50:21,380 --> 00:50:22,550
You even spent the night with her.

571
00:50:26,260 --> 00:50:28,090
You think Director Shin will find her?

572
00:50:28,390 --> 00:50:30,230
- If he really wanted to...
- He's looking into it.

573
00:50:30,990 --> 00:50:33,630
- You can't check immigration, right?
- Right.

574
00:50:34,360 --> 00:50:36,030
That's Reporter Geum for you, though.

575
00:50:37,000 --> 00:50:38,870
- What is?
- Her pride.

576
00:50:39,900 --> 00:50:42,870
Honestly, Ju Shin's love was one-sided.
Reporter Geum was just playing along.

577
00:50:43,870 --> 00:50:46,940
She grew up in that orphanage,
so she probably agreed out of obligation,

578
00:50:47,210 --> 00:50:48,510
but then realized she couldn't
go through with it.

579
00:50:48,850 --> 00:50:49,950
A loveless marriage.

580
00:50:51,850 --> 00:50:53,620
I bet she really went to Boston this time.

581
00:51:11,500 --> 00:51:13,540
She just couldn't take it anymore.

582
00:51:13,970 --> 00:51:16,640
She's been pining for Ha Yong Joong
for almost 20 years.

583
00:51:27,150 --> 00:51:29,020
Is there anything
Yong Joong particularly likes?

584
00:51:29,020 --> 00:51:30,650
He's not a picky eater.

585
00:51:31,960 --> 00:51:32,960
But still.

586
00:51:33,220 --> 00:51:35,430
Grilled fish.
He prefers it over soups or stews.

587
00:51:36,530 --> 00:51:38,030
But grilling fish makes
the whole place smell.

588
00:51:41,560 --> 00:51:43,800
Did Reporter Geum come over often?

589
00:51:44,530 --> 00:51:46,540
I don't think so. Not while I was here.

590
00:51:48,810 --> 00:51:49,810
What are you making?

591
00:51:50,210 --> 00:51:51,210
Vietnamese spring rolls.

592
00:51:51,210 --> 00:51:52,280
Forget that.

593
00:51:52,280 --> 00:51:54,580
You know, that dish where you stuff
minced meat and pan-fry it?

594
00:51:54,980 --> 00:51:58,010
- Make that instead.
- Stuff the meat into what?

595
00:51:58,450 --> 00:51:59,450
Bell peppers.

596
00:52:01,380 --> 00:52:02,720
But I've already prepped
everything for this.

597
00:52:03,890 --> 00:52:04,890
Take it home and eat it.

598
00:52:05,490 --> 00:52:06,490
How many people are in your family?

599
00:52:06,820 --> 00:52:07,820
Three of us.

600
00:52:08,590 --> 00:52:09,660
Are they girls or boys?

601
00:52:10,530 --> 00:52:11,530
Two daughters.

602
00:52:13,160 --> 00:52:14,160
Are you divorced?

603
00:52:15,060 --> 00:52:16,130
I'm a widow.

604
00:52:27,210 --> 00:52:28,680
You're a monster, Director Shin.

605
00:52:30,410 --> 00:52:32,020
You don't get to mess with my head.

606
00:52:46,760 --> 00:52:48,570
Did you leave because I'm that scary
and horrible to you?

607
00:52:56,670 --> 00:52:57,710
She's quite the princess.

608
00:53:03,780 --> 00:53:04,780
My goodness.

609
00:53:05,550 --> 00:53:08,480
It's a boy.
He finally decided to show us today.

610
00:53:11,920 --> 00:53:12,920
Right here.

611
00:53:25,200 --> 00:53:26,740
You don't want to mess with me.

612
00:53:28,240 --> 00:53:29,940
And here I was, about to wish you well.

613
00:54:02,470 --> 00:54:05,010
(Wongyeong Pharmacy)

614
00:54:09,110 --> 00:54:10,350
Yes, that'll be nine dollars.

615
00:54:10,410 --> 00:54:12,050
(Pregnancy test)

616
00:54:13,550 --> 00:54:15,720
I'll take one more, a different brand.

617
00:54:27,060 --> 00:54:29,200
(Pregnancy test)

618
00:54:33,870 --> 00:54:36,240
You're pregnant. You're five weeks along.

619
00:55:05,900 --> 00:55:09,340
(Yong Joong)

620
00:55:10,810 --> 00:55:12,710
(Yong Joong)

621
00:55:22,990 --> 00:55:23,990
What's up?

622
00:55:26,520 --> 00:55:27,790
Are you meeting someone here?

623
00:55:31,660 --> 00:55:32,830
No, I was just around.

624
00:55:35,700 --> 00:55:36,700
What about you?

625
00:55:37,800 --> 00:55:39,400
I was just heading out for a walk,

626
00:55:40,570 --> 00:55:41,570
and there you were.

627
00:55:45,880 --> 00:55:47,410
Didn't you work out this morning?

628
00:55:48,850 --> 00:55:50,810
- No.
- Then go do it.

629
00:55:53,120 --> 00:55:54,120
Have you had lunch?

630
00:55:54,950 --> 00:55:57,220
- Not yet.
- It's after two. Why not?

631
00:55:59,360 --> 00:56:01,690
- What about you?
- I haven't eaten either.

632
00:56:02,260 --> 00:56:03,730
I had an early meeting.

633
00:56:05,660 --> 00:56:07,500
You said this place
has good cold noodles, right?

634
00:56:09,230 --> 00:56:10,230
Let's go.

635
00:56:22,110 --> 00:56:23,110
Cold noodles with broth?

636
00:56:23,410 --> 00:56:24,410
Spicy noodles.

637
00:56:28,990 --> 00:56:30,920
- One broth, one spicy cold noodles.
- Okay.

638
00:56:31,890 --> 00:56:33,690
But you like spicy cold noodles too.

639
00:56:35,360 --> 00:56:36,630
So you can have mine
if yours is too spicy.

640
00:56:36,960 --> 00:56:38,560
Last time, you said it was a little spicy.

641
00:56:40,500 --> 00:56:42,230
I can just take some of the sauce out.

642
00:56:50,310 --> 00:56:51,340
How are you feeling?

643
00:56:52,840 --> 00:56:53,840
I'm fine.

644
00:56:55,880 --> 00:56:57,380
You look a little pale.

645
00:57:03,990 --> 00:57:05,150
How are the wedding plans going?

646
00:57:06,020 --> 00:57:08,160
Fine. There isn't much to do.

647
00:57:09,560 --> 00:57:10,590
I heard from my brother.

648
00:57:11,190 --> 00:57:12,360
You went for your dress fitting.

649
00:57:18,730 --> 00:57:21,570
Okay, just a natural,
conversational vibe, please.

650
00:58:08,020 --> 00:58:10,090
They're always so quick
at cold noodle places.

651
00:58:10,350 --> 00:58:12,460
The popular places
are constantly boiling noodles.

652
00:58:40,980 --> 00:58:41,980
Vinegar.

653
00:58:57,670 --> 00:58:59,770
I just don't get the appeal
of Pyeongyang-style cold noodles.

654
00:59:00,570 --> 00:59:03,340
My boss is a total Pyeongyang-style
cold noodles fanatic, though.

655
00:59:04,510 --> 00:59:05,780
Are you going back to work next year?

656
00:59:07,610 --> 00:59:08,610
No.

657
00:59:09,380 --> 00:59:11,110
Ju Shin doesn't want you to work, does he?

658
00:59:23,490 --> 00:59:24,490
Are you happy?

659
00:59:29,030 --> 00:59:30,230
It was your dream...

660
00:59:31,200 --> 00:59:32,670
to be with Momo,
whom you were so crazy about.

661
00:59:33,370 --> 00:59:34,870
I wouldn't call it a dream.

662
00:59:37,440 --> 00:59:39,580
She's not the same Momo you used to love.

663
00:59:47,480 --> 00:59:48,480
Is it too spicy for you?

664
00:59:48,990 --> 00:59:49,990
Is it okay?

665
00:59:57,060 --> 01:00:00,200
(Bukhyang Noodle House)

666
01:00:05,200 --> 01:00:06,200
Hey.

667
01:00:09,310 --> 01:00:10,470
By the way,

668
01:00:10,870 --> 01:00:12,170
you know...

669
01:00:16,610 --> 01:00:18,610
What kind of gift would you want from me?

670
01:00:19,050 --> 01:00:20,120
If you were to get one.

671
01:00:21,420 --> 01:00:22,490
A wedding gift?

672
01:00:25,190 --> 01:00:26,320
I should be the one getting you a gift.

673
01:00:27,390 --> 01:00:28,720
There's nothing I really need.

674
01:00:31,930 --> 01:00:32,930
Me neither.

675
01:00:43,370 --> 01:00:44,440
I'm glad...

676
01:00:45,980 --> 01:00:47,940
- you are enjoying it.
- It's delicious.

677
01:00:58,850 --> 01:00:59,860
Momo?

678
01:01:00,460 --> 01:01:01,460
No.

679
01:01:02,020 --> 01:01:03,090
The head of marketing.

680
01:01:03,160 --> 01:01:04,430
(Looks like only Tuesday
works for next week.)

681
01:01:21,040 --> 01:01:22,040
What's wrong?

682
01:01:22,580 --> 01:01:23,580
It's spicy.

683
01:01:24,610 --> 01:01:25,610
You should stop then.

684
01:01:26,350 --> 01:01:27,420
No, I'm okay.

685
01:01:27,880 --> 01:01:28,880
Here, have mine.

686
01:01:51,140 --> 01:01:52,840
Is there a convenience store around here?

687
01:01:53,910 --> 01:01:55,040
There's one over there.

688
01:01:56,350 --> 01:01:57,750
I want an ice-cream bar.

689
01:01:58,450 --> 01:02:01,450
Wouldn't a drink be better for spicy food?

690
01:02:02,650 --> 01:02:03,650
Ice cream.

691
01:02:21,570 --> 01:02:23,810
- I'll get the ice cream.
- Just buy me something expensive later.

692
01:02:29,210 --> 01:02:30,210
Okay.

693
01:02:39,620 --> 01:02:41,260
I guess you and Ju Shin
don't keep secrets from each other.

694
01:02:42,830 --> 01:02:44,290
He seemed to know all about us.

695
01:02:49,000 --> 01:02:50,000
Does that bother you?

696
01:02:51,200 --> 01:02:52,200
No.

697
01:02:53,100 --> 01:02:54,970
We never used to keep secrets
from each other.

698
01:03:04,680 --> 01:03:07,620
I realized that I didn't
really know Ju Shin completely...

699
01:03:10,050 --> 01:03:11,190
after I heard about the wedding.

700
01:03:19,300 --> 01:03:20,300
Anyway...

701
01:03:23,970 --> 01:03:26,540
Call me if you need anything.
Or if you want to talk something over.

702
01:03:30,410 --> 01:03:31,470
You know, in life,

703
01:03:32,680 --> 01:03:34,140
unexpected things can happen.

704
01:03:37,550 --> 01:03:38,550
Right?

705
01:03:40,180 --> 01:03:41,520
Momo wouldn't like that.

706
01:03:45,860 --> 01:03:47,220
What's between us
has nothing to do with Momo.

707
01:03:58,700 --> 01:03:59,700
What if...

708
01:04:01,300 --> 01:04:02,500
This is just a hypothetical, but...

709
01:04:07,440 --> 01:04:08,440
Never mind.

710
01:04:10,050 --> 01:04:11,050
Go ahead.

711
01:04:13,380 --> 01:04:14,720
It was great eating with you today.

712
01:04:16,420 --> 01:04:17,550
I was starving.

713
01:04:20,420 --> 01:04:22,590
I was really craving cold noodles.

714
01:04:23,190 --> 01:04:24,530
The kind you treat me to.

715
01:04:27,200 --> 01:04:28,830
You're already so skinny.
Don't go around skipping meals.

716
01:04:30,500 --> 01:04:31,870
Are you sure you don't want
anything to drink?

717
01:04:36,010 --> 01:04:37,170
I don't want to part ways.

718
01:04:38,140 --> 01:04:39,610
I want to stay with you a little longer.

719
01:04:42,040 --> 01:04:43,050
I'm too full.

720
01:04:48,080 --> 01:04:49,490
No, I'll throw it away.

721
01:05:12,840 --> 01:05:13,940
It's dried up.

722
01:05:26,590 --> 01:05:27,660
Take good care of yourself...

723
01:05:29,160 --> 01:05:30,160
so I don't worry.

724
01:05:31,590 --> 01:05:32,960
It's not that I don't want
to worry about you.

725
01:05:38,730 --> 01:05:39,800
You too.

726
01:05:43,570 --> 01:05:44,570
What were you going to say before?

727
01:05:46,780 --> 01:05:48,510
I forgot.

728
01:05:52,410 --> 01:05:53,420
Some other time.

729
01:05:56,190 --> 01:05:57,190
The truth is...

730
01:05:58,520 --> 01:05:59,760
I went to the cafe...

731
01:06:00,860 --> 01:06:01,920
hoping I might run into you.

732
01:06:06,000 --> 01:06:07,500
Wait here, I'll go get the car.

733
01:06:09,230 --> 01:06:10,530
No, if you're going to walk,
I'll walk with you.

734
01:06:10,800 --> 01:06:11,800
I'll wait here.

735
01:07:22,910 --> 01:07:24,870
The phone is turned off.

736
01:07:24,870 --> 01:07:27,880
Please leave a message after the tone.

737
01:07:28,140 --> 01:07:29,180
Charges will apply...

738
01:07:29,180 --> 01:07:30,450
(Ba Ra)

739
01:07:41,920 --> 01:07:44,730
Microwave the rockfish soup
for two minutes.

740
01:09:28,130 --> 01:09:29,130
Honey.

741
01:09:29,670 --> 01:09:31,870
We should've picked a cuter nickname
for the baby.

742
01:09:33,040 --> 01:09:34,340
It's plenty cute.

743
01:09:34,670 --> 01:09:36,910
I just don't think it suits a girl.

744
01:09:37,570 --> 01:09:38,670
What's wrong with Wani?

745
01:09:39,270 --> 01:09:40,280
It sounds like "You're here?"

746
01:09:44,110 --> 01:09:46,420
Don't tell me you're disappointed,
hoping for a boy.

747
01:09:48,580 --> 01:09:50,690
- They bought the expensive one.
- I'll add more...

748
01:09:50,750 --> 01:09:52,390
- Oh, this one?
- Yes.

749
01:09:53,720 --> 01:09:54,720
Here you go.

750
01:10:00,000 --> 01:10:01,000
Puffed rice!

751
01:10:04,400 --> 01:10:07,370
Tangerines, a basket for ten dollars!
Apples, a basket for ten dollars.

752
01:10:07,440 --> 01:10:09,040
Sir, would you like to try an apple?

753
01:10:10,510 --> 01:10:12,170
- How much are they?
- Ten dollars a basket.

754
01:10:12,240 --> 01:10:14,140
- Ten dollars?
- Yes.

755
01:10:14,210 --> 01:10:15,710
(Honey Apples, Ten dollars)

756
01:10:37,800 --> 01:10:38,870
Excuse me!

757
01:10:39,200 --> 01:10:41,300
I'll take one of these hairtails, please.

758
01:11:14,940 --> 01:11:16,070
If there are any spirits listening,

759
01:11:20,180 --> 01:11:21,580
please help me find my child.

760
01:11:27,120 --> 01:11:28,120
Please.

761
01:11:29,720 --> 01:11:33,460
(Hospital Director, Shin Ju Shin)

762
01:11:35,920 --> 01:11:38,060
- I see you called.
- Did you find anything in Boston?

763
01:11:38,360 --> 01:11:40,000
I managed to track down the nun,

764
01:11:40,760 --> 01:11:42,100
but she said she hasn't heard a thing
from Ba Ra.

765
01:11:43,200 --> 01:11:45,030
Do you think Ba Ra told her to say that?

766
01:11:46,740 --> 01:11:47,740
No.

767
01:11:50,640 --> 01:11:52,070
So we're really out of options?

768
01:12:27,380 --> 01:12:30,650
Goodness, Mr. Kim. Hello.

769
01:12:31,010 --> 01:12:32,010
What brings you here?

770
01:13:06,080 --> 01:13:09,020
(Doctor Shin)

771
01:13:09,120 --> 01:13:10,550
When are you due?

772
01:13:10,950 --> 01:13:12,490
Are you about six months along?

773
01:13:12,590 --> 01:13:14,760
- The 12th of next month.
- Momo.

774
01:13:15,460 --> 01:13:17,990
She's getting what she deserves.

775
01:13:18,590 --> 01:13:20,500
- I'm taking a picture.
- Oh my gosh!

776
01:13:20,660 --> 01:13:24,600
Park Sun Woo said she just saw
Reporter Geum at a rest stop.

777
01:13:24,670 --> 01:13:26,470
- Reporter Geum Ba Ra?
- But...

778
01:13:26,470 --> 01:13:28,370
- But what?
- She said she looked different.

779
01:13:28,370 --> 01:13:29,440
Looked different?

780
01:13:29,500 --> 01:13:31,310
Hyun Ran Hee visited today.

781
01:13:31,310 --> 01:13:33,710
She just wanted to find our daughter.

782
01:13:33,780 --> 01:13:35,080
"Our daughter?"

783
01:13:35,080 --> 01:13:37,750
Have you heard about Geum Ba Ra?

784
01:13:38,310 --> 01:13:40,980
- Have you?
- I'm worried she's trembling somewhere.

785
01:13:41,080 --> 01:13:44,320
If they really saw her at Meeting Plaza,
then she must be with someone.

786
01:13:44,390 --> 01:13:46,660
Do you think Ba Ra ever thinks about us?

787
01:13:46,660 --> 01:13:47,760
She probably doesn't think of me.

788
01:13:48,420 --> 01:13:50,390
- You?
- Don't you dare compare me to him!

789
01:13:50,960 --> 01:13:51,960
You're so two-faced.

790
01:13:51,960 --> 01:13:53,800
Then go find your precious, pregnant Ba Ra
and live together.

791
01:13:53,900 --> 01:13:55,330
Didn't you say James's employee saw her?

792
